nfants and revealing the bankruptcy of contemporary questionnaire-based personality theory. More broadly, Kagan’s daring, thoroughly informed, and keenly reasoned book demonstrates the risks of making generalizations about human behavior, in which culture, context, and past experience play such paramount and unpredictable roles.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aCognition. 0aPerception. 0aSchemas (Psychology). 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Developmental / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674274341zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674274341423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674274341/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK